<bean parent="Uif-Disclosure-TableCollectionSection" p:layoutManager.numberOfColumns="4">
  <property name="collectionObjectClass" value="org.kuali.rice.krad.demo.uif.form.UITestObject"/>
  <property name="propertyName" value="collection1"/>
  <property name="layoutManager.sequencePropertyName" value="field1"/>
  <property name="layoutManager.generateAutoSequence" value ="false"/>
  <property name="layoutManager.sequenceFieldPrototype">
    <bean parent="Uif-InputField" p:propertyName="field1" p:readOnly="true"/>
  </property>
  <property name="layoutManager.richTable.render" value="true"/>
  <property name="items">
    <list>
      <bean parent="Uif-InputField" p:propertyName="field1" p:required="true" p:label="Field 1"/>
      <bean parent="Uif-InputField" p:propertyName="field2" p:required="false" p:label="Field 2" p:constraintText="Requires Field 1 be filled out">
        <property name="dependencyConstraints">
          <list>
            <bean parent="PrerequisiteConstraint" p:propertyName="field1"/>
          </list>
        </property>
      </bean>
      <bean parent="Uif-InputField" p:propertyName="field3" p:required="@{1 == 1}" p:label="Field 3"/>
      <bean parent="Uif-InputField" p:propertyName="bfield" p:required="true" p:label="SubField 4">
        <property name="control">
          <bean parent="Uif-CheckboxControl">
            <property name="onChangeScript" value="alert('checkbox clicked')"/>
          </bean>
        </property>
      </bean>
      <bean parent="Uif-DataField" p:propertyName="stringList"  p:label="Read-only Sublist"
            p:readOnlyDisplayReplacement="@{#emptyList(#lp.stringList)?'None Available':''}"/>
    </list>
  </property>
</bean>
<bean parent="Uif-Disclosure-TableCollectionSection" p:layoutManager.numberOfColumns="4">
  <property name="collectionObjectClass" value="org.kuali.rice.krad.demo.uif.form.UITestObject" />
  <property name="propertyName" value="collection2" />
  <property name="layoutManager.sequencePropertyName" value="field1" />
  <property name="layoutManager.generateAutoSequence" value ="false"/>
  <property name="layoutManager.sequenceFieldPrototype">
    <bean parent="Uif-InputField" p:propertyName="field1" p:readOnly="true"/>
  </property>
  <property name="layoutManager.sequenceFieldPrototype.width" value="10%" />
  <property name="layoutManager.actionFieldPrototype.width" value="10%" />
  <property name="layoutManager.actionColumnPlacement" value="LEFT" />
  <property name="collectionLookup">
    <bean parent="Uif-CollectionQuickFinder"
          p:dataObjectClassName="org.kuali.rice.krad.demo.travel.dataobject.TravelAccount"
          p:fieldConversions="number:field1,name:field2,subAccount:field3,subAccountName:field4"/>
  </property>
  <property name="lineActions">
    <list>
      <bean parent="Uif-SecondaryActionButton-Small" p:methodToCall="customLineAction" p:actionLabel="custom"
            p:actionParameters="field1:@{#line.field1},field2:@{#line.field2}"/>
    </list>
  </property>
  <property name="items">
    <list>
      <bean parent="Uif-InputField" p:propertyName="field1" p:required="true" p:width="20%" p:render="@{false}" p:label="Field 1"/>
      <bean parent="Uif-InputField" p:propertyName="field2" p:wrapperCssClasses="hello" p:required="true" p:readOnly="true" p:width="20%" p:label="Field 2"/>
      <bean parent="Uif-InputField" p:propertyName="field3" p:required="true" p:width="20%" p:label="Field 3"/>
      <bean parent="Uif-InputField" p:propertyName="field4" p:required="true" p:width="20%" p:label="Field 4" p:constraintText="Field 1A; AND/OR Field 2A with Field 2B must occur when this field has a value">
        <property name="mustOccurConstraints">
          <list>
            <bean parent="MustOccurConstraint">
              <property name="min" value="1" />
              <property name="max" value="2" />
              <property name="prerequisiteConstraints">
                <list>
                  <bean parent="PrerequisiteConstraint" p:propertyName="field1" />
                </list>
              </property>
              <!-- essentially an OR'ed list: each MustOccur constraint in this
    list essentially counts towards the min max totals set at the top level,
    they are equivalent to having a PrerequisiteConstraint satisfied at the top
    level (count as one towards the total) so this constraint is saying you can
    fill out just field11 or you can fill out both field12 and field13, in addition
    filling out all 3 fields is fine in this context -->
              <property name="mustOccurConstraints">
                <list>
                  <bean parent="MustOccurConstraint">
                    <property name="min" value="2" />
                    <property name="max" value="2" />
                    <property name="prerequisiteConstraints">
                      <list>
                        <bean parent="PrerequisiteConstraint" p:propertyName="field2" />
                        <bean parent="PrerequisiteConstraint" p:propertyName="field3" />
                      </list>
                    </property>
                  </bean>
                </list>
              </property>
            </bean>
          </list>
        </property>
      </bean>
    </list>
  </property>
  <property name="filters">
    <list>
      <bean parent="Uif-ConditionalCollectionFilter" p:expression="#line.field1 ne '1'"/>
    </list>
  </property>
</bean>

Developer Documentation
 Class JavaDocKRAD Guide
Implementation of table layout manager.

Based on the fields defined, the TableLayoutManager will dynamically create instances of
the fields for each collection row. In addition, the manager can create standard fields like the
action and sequence fields for each row. The manager supports options inherited from the
GridLayoutManager such as rowSpan, colSpan, and cell width settings.

{@inheritDoc}
Preconfigured KRAD Schema Names & Bean ids
Schema NameUif Bean Id
tableCollectionLayout-beanUif-TableCollectionLayout
Properties
actionColumnPlacement
String
Indicates the actions column placement


Valid values are 'LEFT', 'RIGHT' or any valid number. The default is 'RIGHT' or '-1'. The
column placement index takes all displayed columns, including sequence and selection columns,
into account.

actionFieldPrototype
FieldGroup
FieldGroup instance to serve as a prototype for the actions column. For each
collection line this instance is copied and adjusted as necessary. Note the actual actions
for the group come from the collection groups actions List
(org.kuali.rice.krad.uif.container.CollectionGroup.getActions()). The FieldGroup prototype is
useful for setting styling of the actions column and for the layout of the action fields.
Note also the label associated with the prototype is used for the action column header
ajaxDetailsRetrieval
boolean
If true, when a row details open action is performed, it will get the details content from
the server the first time it is opened. The methodToCall will be a component "refresh" call
by default (this can be set on expandDetailsActionPrototype) and the additional action
parameters sent to the server will be those set on the expandDetailsActionPrototype
(lineIndex will be sent by default).
applyAlternatingRowStyles
boolean
Indicates whether alternating row styles should be applied.

Indicator to layout manager templates to apply alternating row styles.
See the configured template for the actual style classes used
applyDefaultCellWidths
boolean
Indicates whether the manager should default the cell widths.

If true, the manager will set the cell width by equally dividing by the
number of columns
autoTruncateColumns
Boolean
NO DOCUMENTATION AVAILABLE... we are working on it!
columnCalculations
List
Gets the column calculations. This is a list of ColumnCalcuationInfo that when set provides
calculations to be performed on the columns they specify. These calculations appear in the
table's footer. This feature is only available when using richTable functionality.
conditionalRowCssClasses
Map
NO DOCUMENTATION AVAILABLE... we are working on it!
expandDetailsActionPrototype
Action
The Action prototype used for the row details expand link. Should be set to
"Uif-ExpandDetailsAction" or "Uif-ExpandDetailsImageAction". Properties can be configured to
allow for different methodToCall and actionParameters to be set for ajax row details
retrieval.
generateAutoSequence
boolean
Indicates whether the sequence field should be generated with the current line number


If set to true the sequence field prototype will be changed to a message field (if not
already a message field) and the text will be set to the current line number

groupTotalLabelPrototype
Label
The groupTotal label to use when renderOnlyLeftTotalLabels is TRUE. This label will appear in
the left most column.
groupingPrefix
String
Get the groupingPrefix. The groupingPrefix is used to prefix the generated title (not used
when groupingTitle is set directly) when using groupingPropertyNames.
groupingPropertyNames
List
Gets the list of property names to use for grouping.


When this property is set, grouping for this collection will be enabled and the lines of the
collection will be grouped by the propertyName(s) supplied. Supplying multiple property names
will cause the grouping to be on multiple fields and ordered alphabetically on
"propetyValue1, propertyValue2" (this is also how the group title will display for each
group). The property names supplied must be relative to the line, so #lp SHOULD NOT be used
(it is assumed automatically).

groupingTitle
String
Get the groupingTitle. The groupingTitle MUST contain a SpringEL expression to uniquely
identify a group's line (ie it cannot be a static string because each group must be
identified by some value). This overrides groupingPropertyNames(if set) because it
provides full control of grouping value used by the collection. SpringEL defined here must
use #lp if referencing values of the line.
headerLabelPrototype
Label
Label instance to use as a prototype for creating the tables header fields. For each
header field the prototype will be copied and adjusted as necessary
hiddenColumns
Set
Gets a set of property names defining hidden columns.
numberOfColumns
int
Indicates the number of columns that should make up one row of data.

If the item count is greater than the number of columns, a new row will
be created to render the remaining items (and so on until all items are
placed).


Note this does not include any generated columns by the layout manager,
so the final column count could be greater (if label fields are
separate).
numberOfDataColumns
int
{@inheritDoc}
pageTotalLabel
Label
The pageTotal label to use when renderOnlyLeftTotalLabels is TRUE for total. This label will
appear in the left most column.
renderOnlyLeftTotalLabels
boolean
When true, labels for the totals fields will only appear in the left most column. Showing of
the totals is controlled by the settings on the TableLayoutManager itself when this property
is true.
renderSequenceField
boolean
Indicates whether the sequence field should be rendered for the collection
repeatHeader
boolean
Indicates whether the header should be repeated before each collection row. If false the
header is only rendered at the beginning of the table
richTable
RichTable
Widget associated with the table to add functionality such as sorting, paging, and export
rowCssClasses
List
List of styles for each row.

Each entry in the list gives the style for the row with the same index. This style will be added to
the  tag when the table rows are rendered in the grid.tag. This is used to store the styles for newly added lines
and other special cases like the add item row.
rowDataAttributes
List
List of data attributes for each row.

Each entry in the list gives the data attributes for the row with the same index. These data attributes will be added to
the  tag when the table rows are rendered in the grid.tag. This is used to store the data attributes for newly added lines
and other special cases like the add item row.
rowDetailsGroup
Group
The row details info group to use when using a TableLayoutManager with the a richTable.


This group will be displayed when the user clicks the "Details" link/image on a row. This
allows extra/long data to be hidden in table rows and then revealed during interaction with
the table without the need to leave the page. Allows for any group content.




Does not currently work with javascript required content.

rowDetailsOpen
boolean
If true, all details will be opened by default when the table loads. Can only be used on
tables that have row details setup.
separateAddLine
boolean
Indicates whether the add line should be rendered in a separate group, or as part of the
table (first line)


When separate add line is enabled, the fields for the add line will be placed in the
#getAddLineGroup(). This group can be used to configure the add line presentation. In
addition to the fields, the header on the group (unless already set) will be set to
org.kuali.rice.krad.uif.container.CollectionGroup#getAddLabel() and the add line
actions will be placed into the group's footer.

sequenceFieldPrototype
Field
Field instance to serve as a prototype for the sequence field. For each collection
line this instance is copied and adjusted as necessary
sequencePropertyName
String
Attribute name to use as sequence value. For each collection line the value of this field on
the line will be retrieved and used as the sequence value
showGroupTotal
boolean
Gets showGroupTotal. showGroupTotal shows/calculates the total field for each grouping when
true (and only when the table actually has grouping turned on), otherwise it is not rendered. 

Only used when renderOnlyLeftTotalLabels is TRUE, this overrides the
ColumnConfigurationInfo setting. Otherwise, the ColumnConfigurationInfo setting takes
precedence.
showPageTotal
boolean
Gets showTotal. showTotal shows/calculates the total field when true, otherwise it is not
rendered. 

Only used when renderOnlyLeftTotalLabels is TRUE, this overrides the
ColumnConfigurationInfo setting. Otherwise, the ColumnConfigurationInfo setting takes
precedence.
showToggleAllDetails
boolean
If true, the toggleAllDetailsAction will be shown. This button allows all details to be
open/closed simultaneously.
showTotal
boolean
Gets showTotal. showTotal shows/calculates the total field when true, otherwise it is not
rendered. 

Only used when renderOnlyLeftTotalLabels is TRUE, this overrides the
ColumnConfigurationInfo setting. Otherwise, the ColumnConfigurationInfo setting takes
precedence.
sortableColumns
Set
Gets a set of property names defining sortable columns.
suppressLineWrapping
boolean
Indicates whether the number of columns for the table data should match
the number of fields given in the container's items list (so that each
field takes up one column without wrapping), this overrides the configured
numberOfColumns.

If set to true during the initialize phase the number of columns will be
set to the size of the container's field list, if false the configured
number of columns is used
toggleAllDetailsAction
Action
The toggleAllDetailsAction action component used to toggle all row details open/closed. This
property is set by the default configuration and should not be reset in most cases.
totalLabel
Label
The total label to use when renderOnlyLeftTotalLabels is TRUE for total. This label will
appear in the left most column.
useShortLabels
boolean
Indicates whether the short label for the collection field should be used as the table header
or the regular label

About KRAD


Kuali Rapid Application Development (KRAD) is a framework that eases the
development of enterprise web applications by providing reusable solutions and tooling that enables
developers to build in a rapid and agile fashion. KRAD is a complete framework for web developers
that provides infrastructure in all the major areas of an application (client, business, and data),
and integrates with other modules of the Rice middleware project. In future releases, KNS will be
absorbed into and replaced by KRAD.
